==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: newsroom
<hw>news"room`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A room where news
is collected and disseminated, located in the offices of a newspaper,
magazine, or news broadcast organization; <as>as, the CBS
<ex>newsroom</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A room where periodicals are sold; a reading room
supplied with newspapers, magazines, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>News-vender</ent>⟦br⟧
